Interface ThrowingIntConsumer1

  • All Superinterfaces:

    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ThrowingIntConsumer1
extends AbstractThrowingIntConsumer1<AbstractThrowingIntConsumer1.Handler,ThrowingIntConsumer1>
    Represents an operation that accepts a int-valued argument and returns no result or throws a throwable. This is the one-arity specialization of ThrowingConsumerN. This is the non-producing specialization of ThrowingFunction1. This is the int-consuming primitive specialization of ThrowingConsumer1. this is the throwing variation of IntConsumer1.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is AbstractThrowingIntConsumer1.accept(int).

    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    ThrowingConsumerN, ThrowingFunction1, ThrowingConsumer1, IntConsumer1
